&lt;p&gt;The essential responsibilities of this position, while not limited to the following, will include:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnership &amp;amp; Market Facing Leadership (50%):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as Relay&#39;s primary ambassador across Tennessee, cultivating and sustaining relationships with district, charter, state, and community stakeholders to advance Relay&#39;s mission and impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, engage, and develop strategic partnerships that strengthen Relay&#39;s presence across the state and support growth and long-term sustainability of Relay programs in Tennessee&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage existing professional networks and build new relationships with influential education leaders, decision-makers, and organizations to expand awareness of Relay programs and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Relay at state, regional, and local convenings, positioning the institution as a trusted thought partner within Tennessee&#39;s education ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share program outcomes and data with internal and external stakeholders to demonstrate impact, strengthen partnerships, and inform continuous improvement efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with finance and development teams to ensure grant structures are streamlined, compliant, and aligned with program goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute key local and institutional projects aligned with Relay’s strategic plan, as defined by the Vice Provost, Teacher Preparation, and Dean of Clinical Experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain strong communication with school partners to support student success and Educator Preparation Program (EPP) completion, including progress updates, advisory boards, and data sharing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
